Design and build my portfolio website with a Vercel-inspired monochrome aesthetic — strictly black, white, and grays only. The design philosophy is: less is more. Every element must earn its place.
Background & Atmosphere:

Background color: #080808 — not pure black, a rich off-black with depth
Add an extremely subtle noise/grain texture over the background (CSS or SVG filter) — just enough to feel tactile, not visible at a glance
Very faint radial gradient centered at the top: from #111 to #080808 — creates a soft light source without being decorative
The grain + gradient combo should make the background feel alive without adding any obvious visual elements

Typography:

Display/headings: Geist, ABC Diatype, or Söhne — sharp, geometric, high-contrast
Body: same family, lighter weight
Name rendered large (but not oversized) in #ffffff with letter-spacing: -0.02em
All secondary text in #666 — never pure gray, slightly warm

Unique Signature Details:

A single 1px horizontal rule in #1a1a1a separates each section — barely visible, more felt than seen
On hover over project titles: text color shifts from #666 to #fff with a 200ms ease — clean, intentional
A blinking cursor character | after the name on load, disappears after 2 seconds
Footer has a tiny "Currently available for work" indicator — a 6px circle in #fff with a soft CSS pulse animation, followed by the text in #444

Layout Rules:

Single-column, max-width 660px, centered
Sections separated by thin lines, not cards or boxes
Navigation: just text links, no nav bars or hamburger menus
NO icons unless absolutely necessary
NO hero images, background textures beyond the grain, or illustrations

Sections (in order):

Name + one-line role description
Short bio (2–3 sentences max)
Selected Work — project title, year, one-line description, link
Experience — company, role, year range
Contact — just an email link

Micro-interactions:

Page fade-in on load: opacity 0 → 1, 400ms, ease-out
Underline slides in on link hover
Everything else is static — no scroll animations, no parallax